03/05/85 setdisk

Syntax as a command:  setdisk


Function:  schedules the absentee job that performs disk reporting.
Unless the absentee job crashes or the absentee job queues are lost,
there is no need to execute this command.  To check whether a job is
scheduled, invoke the list_absentee_request command (described in the
Multics Commands and Active Functions manual, Order No.  AG92).
